Plugins, particularly Greenhopper, often seem to need a re-index after they've been installed or upgraded, or after some kinds of configuration changes have been made.

Rather than relying on the sysadmin to manually intervene, it would be particularly helpful if an API call were available that any plugin could call, to indicate to JIRA that a re-index is needed (invocations subsequent to the first could be turned into a no-op). JIRA could then check for this flag during startup or at the end of the upgrade process, and automatically rebuild its indices before making the system available to users.

This won't obviate _all_ need for manually kicking off a re-index, but it would certainly catch many cases.

